{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600045","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600045"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:00:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:00:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15599"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15599","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15599"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.29,0.1,0,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8290"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70392"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8290"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15599"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55856"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5103"},{"type":"tags","id":"8189"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20013"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20017"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70392","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70392"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA thyroid biopsy specimen shows hyperplastic follicular epithelial cells with a columnar appearance. The colloid appears scalloped at the edges, and there is diffuse lymphocytic infiltration throughout the tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely histological diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hashimoto thyroiditis","Lymphocytic thyroiditis","Subacute granulomatous thyroiditis","Fibrous thyroiditis","Graves disease"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features shown are characteristic of \u003Cstrong\u003EGraves disease\u003C/strong\u003E, including tall columnar follicular cells, scalloped colloid, and lymphocytic infiltration. These changes reflect the hyperactive state of the thyroid gland stimulated by thyroid-stimulating immunoglobulins.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect diagnoses can be distinguished by their characteristic features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHashimoto thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E shows extensive lymphoid infiltration with germinal centre formation and H\u00fcrthle cell changes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphocytic thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates dense lymphocytic infiltration without the hyperplastic changes seen in Graves disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubacute granulomatous thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E shows granulomas and giant cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrous thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by dense fibrosis extending beyond the thyroid capsule\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe combination of hyperplastic follicular cells, scalloped colloid and lymphocytic infiltration is diagnostic of Graves disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Graves disease shows characteristic histological features including hyperplastic follicular cells, scalloped colloid, and lymphoid infiltrates","Graves disease is the most common cause of hyperthyroidism in Australia","Histological features help distinguish between different types of thyroiditis"],"references":["\u0022Subacute thyroiditis - intermed mag\u0022 by Nephron is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Subacute_thyroiditis_-_intermed_mag.jpg","Bhadauria RS, Nema SK, Kumar P. De Quervain\u0027s Thyroiditis. Med J Armed Forces India. 2003 Oct;59(4):347-8. doi: 10.1016/S0377-1237(03)80154-5. Epub 2011 Jul 21. PMID: 27407560; PMCID: PMC4923540.","De Leo S, Lee SY, Braverman LE. Hyperthyroidism. Lancet. 2016 Aug 27;388(10047):906-918. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(16)00278-6. Epub 2016 Mar 30. PMID: 27038492; PMCID: PMC5014602","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55856"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15599"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21171"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21171","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21171"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/NZ6wJssjmMiS4Qbu22hXWJZY8BHKmp.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/NZ6wJssjmMiS4Qbu22hXWJZY8BHKmp.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1000}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55856"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T20:22:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T20:29:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8290"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70392"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":n